The paper addresses the task of makeup transfer, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques, indicating that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a GAN, which is a popular deep learning technique used in image generation and manipulation, further supporting the likelihood of it belonging to cs.CV. The paper also mentions the use of spatial-aware makeup matrices and an attentive makeup morphing module, which suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a dataset for evaluations, indicating that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a distillation network and the ability to perform partial and shade-controllable makeup transfer, suggesting that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
